."},{"id":"regiment19-1","name":"2nd (Chiskirkwar) Regiment","legend":"Regiment was formed in 1590 Westcker Era during the Soutfieldian Crusade. 2nd (Chiskirkwar) Regiment is stationed in Chiskirkwar County. \r\n\r\nRegiment composition in 1715 WE:\r\n— archers: 1473\r\n— cavalry: 264\r\n— infantry: 1291\r\n— artillery: 6."},{"id":"regiment19-2","name":"3rd (Chiskirkwar) Regiment","legend":"Regiment was formed in 1522 Westcker Era during the Chiptontan Conquest. 3rd (Chiskirkwar) Regiment is stationed in Chiskirkwar. \r\n\r\nRegiment composition in 1715 WE:\r\n— archers: 495\r\n— cavalry: 56\r\n— infantry: 381\r\n— artillery: 16."},{"id":"regiment19-3","name":"1st Fleet","legend":"Regiment was formed in 1523 Westcker Era during the Chiptontan Conquest. 1st Fleet is based in Chiskirkwar. \r\n\r\nRegiment composition in 1715 WE:\r\n— fleet: 7."},{"id":"regiment19-4","name":"2nd Fleet","legend":"Regiment was formed in 1710 Westcker Era during the Meter Campaign. 2nd Fleet is based in Soutfield. \r\n\r\nRegiment composition in 1715 WE:\r\n— fleet: 2."},{"id":"marker0","name":"Alther","legend":"Dormant volcano. Height: 6724 m."},{"id":"marker1","name":"Castondole","legend":"A geothermal springs with naturally heated water that provide relaxation and medicinal benefits. Average temperature is 25°C."},{"id":"marker2","name":"Biverham Creek of Luck","legend":"This legendary water source is whispered about in ancient tales and believed to possess mystical properties. The spring emanates crystal-clear water, shimmering with an otherworldly iridescence that sparkles even in the dimmest light."},{"id":"marker3","name":"Waling — silver mining town","legend":"Waling is a mining town of 1496 people just nearby the silver mine."},{"id":"marker4","name":"Tutrinch — salt mining town","legend":"Tutrinch is a mining town of 4476 people just nearby the salt mine."},{"id":"marker5","name":"Chistoney — salt mining town","legend":"Chistoney is a mining town of 15054 people just nearby the salt mine."},{"id":"marker6","name":"Weston — iron mining town","legend":"Weston is a mining town of 1413 people just nearby the iron mine."},{"id":"marker7","name":"Skiple — silver mining town","legend":"Skiple is a mining town of 15624 people just nearby the silver mine."},{"id":"marker8","name":"Marldock Bridge","legend":"An old crossing of the Gramburghel River, rarely used since the old waypoints crumbled."},{"id":"marker9","name":"The Green Rat","legend":"A big and famous roadside tavern. Delicious pan-fried rat with shiny tea is served here."},{"id":"marker10","name":"The Old Inn","legend":"A big and famous roadside inn. Delicious deep-fried chickpea with white gin is served here."},{"id":"marker11","name":"The Good Ibis","legend":"A big and famous roadside tavern. Delicious braised rat tails with light absinthe is served here."},{"id":"marker12","name":"The Golden Inn","legend":"A big and famous roadside inn. Delicious stuffed lamb with fire kvass is served here."},{"id":"marker13","name":"The Flying Tavern","legend":"A big and famous roadside tavern. Delicious pan-fried melon with bright beer is served here."},{"id":"marker14","name":"The Loud Inn","legend":"A big and famous roadside inn. Delicious marinated buffalo with smelly tequila is served here."},{"id":"marker15","name":"Dartonese Lighthouse","legend":"A lighthouse to serve as a beacon for ships in the open sea."},{"id":"marker16","name":"Dunstomer Lighthouse","legend":"A lighthouse to serve as a beacon for ships in the open sea."},{"id":"marker17","name":"Southwelese Lighthouse","legend":"A lighthouse to serve as a beacon for ships in the open sea."},{"id":"marker18","name":"Chawbobury Lighthouse","legend":"A lighthouse to serve as a beacon for ships in the open sea."},{"id":"marker19","name":"Quatham Lighthouse","legend":"A lighthouse to serve as a beacon for ships in the open sea."},{"id":"marker20","name":"Tretonese Lighthouse","legend":"A lighthouse to serve as a beacon for ships in the open sea."},{"id":"marker21","name":"Bramplenilese Lighthouse","legend":"A lighthouse to serve as a beacon for ships in the open sea."},{"id":"marker22","name":"Bolestovilese Waterfall","legend":"A river drops down from a great height forming a wonderous waterfall."},{"id":"marker23","name":"Yeoverling Battlefield","legend":"A historical battle of the Mavetontian War. \r\nDate: October 28, 1695 Westcker Era."},{"id":"marker24","name":"Frampton Battlefield","legend":"A historical battle of the Altrinchian Expedition. \r\nDate: May 19, 1609 Westcker Era."},{"id":"marker25","name":"Rockeroema Battlefield","legend":"A historical battle of the Congford War. \r\nDate: December 15, 1253 Westcker Era."},{"id":"marker26","name":"Dungeon","legend":"<div>Undiscovered dungeon. See <a href=\"https://watabou.github.io/one-page-dungeon/?seed=3462353124364\" target=\"_blank\">One page dungeon</a></div><iframe style=\"pointer-events: none;\" src=\"https://watabou.github.io/one-page-dungeon/?seed=3462353124364\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin\"></iframe>"},{"id":"marker27","name":"Dungeon","legend":"<div>Undiscovered dungeon. See <a href=\"https://watabou.github.io/one-page-dungeon/?seed=3462353122919\" target=\"_blank\">One page dungeon</a></div><iframe style=\"pointer-events: none;\" src=\"https://watabou.github.io/one-page-dungeon/?seed=3462353122919\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin\"></iframe>"},{"id":"marker28","name":"Dungeon","legend":"<div>Undiscovered dungeon. See <a href=\"https://watabou.github.io/one-page-dungeon/?seed=346235312895\" target=\"_blank\">One page dungeon</a></div><iframe style=\"pointer-events: none;\" src=\"https://watabou.github.io/one-page-dungeon/?seed=346235312895\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin\"></iframe>"},{"id":"marker29","name":"Draxningin Monster","legend":"Locals say a relic monster of 8 m long inhabits Draxningin Lake. Truth or lie, folks are afraid to fish in the lake."},{"id":"marker30","name":"Wasingston Monster","legend":"Rumors say a relic monster of 12 m long inhabits Wasingston Lake. Truth or lie, folks are afraid to fish in the lake."},{"id":"marker31","name":"Thatclif Monster","legend":"Old sailors tell stories of a gigantic sea monster inhabiting these dangerous waters. Rumors say it can be 36 m long."},{"id":"marker32","name":"Winkleigh Monster","legend":"Old sailors tell stories of a gigantic sea monster inhabiting these dangerous waters. Rumors say it can be 11 m long."},{"id":"marker33","name":"Hatfordge Warg","legend":"Rumors speak of a great Warg who inhabits Hatfordge hills and steals cattle at night."},{"id":"marker34","name":"Dunsbury Forest","legend":"A forest sacred to local Boroughism."},{"id":"marker35","name":"Witley Forest","legend":"A forest sacred to local Word of Clifnalton."},{"id":"marker36","name":"Stotbuse Pinery","legend":"A pinery sacred to local Word of Clifnalton."},{"id":"marker37","name":"Westneswest Sharks","legend":"A gang of forest robbers."},{"id":"marker38","name":"Exning Dogs","legend":"A gang of forest brigands."},{"id":"marker39","name":"Dunscom Wolfs","legend":"A gang of forest brigands."},{"id":"marker40","name":"Rocles Lions","legend":"A gang of forest bandits."},{"id":"marker41","name":"Pirates","legend":"Pirate ships have been spotted in these waters."},{"id":"marker42","name":"Pirates","legend":"Pirate ships have been spotted in these waters."},{"id":"marker43","name":"Pirates","legend":"Pirate ships have been spotted in these waters."},{"id":"marker44","name":"Pirates","legend":"Pirate ships have been spotted in these waters."},{"id":"marker45","name":"Pirates","legend":"Pirate ships have been spotted in these waters."},{"id":"marker46","name":"Betleley Monolith","legend":"An ancient monolith. It has an inscription, but no one can translate it:\n        <div style=\"font-size: 1.8em; line-break: anywhere;\">ዐሠ ከነበነፐወዘቀከከነሀ ጰለሠአዘወዘጰሰለከጰጰሠኀገ ረሰነገጸጠከገሰነሀፀወዘቀወጸጰ መ</div>"},{"id":"marker47","name":"Dodbrid Column","legend":"An ancient column. It has an inscription, but no one can translate it:\n        <div style=\"font-size: 1.8em; line-break: anywhere;\">ጰጰበወደየገሰከረረሀጠነ ጠረሠበአየጠጰየፈሠኀአነነኀነጸሰሀፐኀረጸሐ ወረዘ አተሠ </div>"},{"id":"marker48","name":"Covilton Column","legend":"An ancient column. It has an inscription, but no one can translate it:\n        <div style=\"font-size: 1.8em; line-break: anywhere;\">᠀ᡁᡮᢐᡎᡗᡕᢏᠼᠳᢡᡎᢓ᠐ᢤᡟᢜᠮᠠᠵᢒᡭᠱᡲᠼᠨᢒᡱᠵ᠐ᡔᡟᡑᡓᠰᡗᢟᢂᡑᡀᢟᠪᢑ</div>"},{"id":"marker49","name":"Ruined Fortification","legend":"Ruins of an ancient fortification. Untold riches may lie within."},{"id":"marker50","name":"Ruined Town","legend":"Ruins of an ancient town. Untold riches may lie within."},{"id":"marker51","name":"Ruined Town","legend":"Ruins of an ancient town. Untold riches may lie within."},{"id":"marker52","name":"Balney Library","legend":"A vast collection of knowledge, including many rare and ancient tomes."},{"id":"marker53","name":"Travelling Wonderous Circus","legend":"Roll up, roll up, this wonderous circus is here for a limited time only."},{"id":"marker54","name":"Travelling Unmissable Circus","legend":"Roll up, roll up, this unmissable circus is here for a limited time only."},{"id":"marker55","name":"Brorough Contest","legend":"Warriors from around the land gather for a contest of acumen in Brorough, with fame, fortune and favour on offer to the victor."},{"id":"marker56","name":"Perstorough Fair","legend":"A fair is being held in Perstorough, with all manner of local and foreign goods and services on offer."},{"id":"marker57","name":"Minor Jetty","legend":"A small location along the Kingdon River to launch boats from sits here, along with a weary looking owner, willing to sell passage along the river."},{"id":"marker58","name":"Mantises migration","legend":"A huge group of mantises are migrating, whether part of their annual routine, or something more extraordinary."},{"id":"marker59","name":"Chawbigley gala","legend":"A gala has been organised at Chawbigley as a chance to gather the spiritual leaders of the area together to be merry, make alliances and scheme around the crisis."},{"id":"marker60","name":"Chichbutego Fracture","legend":"The Chichbutego Fracture. Locals claim that it is completely flooded."},{"id":"marker61","name":"Clitfordle Sepulchre","legend":"A foreboding necropolis shrouded in perpetual darkness, where eerie whispers echo through the winding corridors and spectral guardians stand watch over the tombs of long-forgotten souls."},{"id":"marker62","name":"Random encounter","legend":"<div>You have encountered a character.</div><iframe src=\"https://deorum.vercel.app/encounter/1185\" width=\"375\" height=\"600\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups\"></iframe>"},{"id":"marker63","name":"Random encounter","legend":"<div>You have encountered a character.</div><iframe src=\"https://deorum.vercel.app/encounter/4257\" width=\"375\" height=\"600\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups\"></iframe>"},{"id":"marker64","name":"Random encounter","legend":"<div>You have encountered a character.</div><iframe src=\"https://deorum.vercel.app/encounter/2645\" width=\"375\" height=\"600\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups\"></iframe>"},{"id":"marker65","name":"Random encounter","legend":"<div>You have encountered a character.</div><iframe src=\"https://deorum.vercel.app/encounter/2042\" width=\"375\" height=\"600\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups\"></iframe>"},{"id":"marker66","name":"Random encounter","legend":"<div>You have encountered a character.</div><iframe src=\"https://deorum.vercel.app/encounter/723\" width=\"375\" height=\"600\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups\"></iframe>"},{"id":"marker67","name":"Random encounter","legend":"<div>You have encountered a character.</div><iframe src=\"https://deorum.vercel.app/encounter/2219\" width=\"375\" height=\"600\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups\"></iframe>"},{"id":"marker68","name":"Random encounter","legend":"<div>You have encountered a character.</div><iframe src=\"https://deorum.vercel.app/encounter/1193\" width=\"375\" height=\"600\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups\"></iframe>"},{"id":"stateLabel6","name":"Kingdom of Misadinu","legend":""}]
